Maintainer: Tyler Muffly <tyler.muffly@dhha.org>
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for scoring, validating, and analyzing 
    patient-reported outcome measures (PROMs) used in urogynecology and pelvic 
    floor medicine. The package implements standardized scoring algorithms for 
    widely-used questionnaires including: the Pelvic Floor Distress Inventory 
    (PFDI-20) with its subscales (POPDI-6, CRADI-8, UDI-6), the Patient Global 
    Impression of Improvement (PGI-I), and the Sandvik Severity Index for urinary 
    incontinence. Core features include: robust validation of input data, 
    evidence-based handling of missing responses according to instrument-specific 
    guidelines, consistent score scaling and interpretation, detailed logging for 
    quality assurance, and comprehensive documentation with clinical context. 
    All scoring methods follow published validation studies and clinical practice 
    guidelines to ensure reproducibility in research and clinical applications. 
    References: Barber et al. (2005) <doi:10.1016/j.ajog.2004.10.578>; 
    Yalcin & Bump (2003) <doi:10.1016/S0002-9378(03)00598-1>; 
    Sandvik et al. (2000) <doi:10.1002/nau.1041>;
    Jelovsek & Barber (2006) <doi:10.1016/j.ajog.2006.01.060>.
